 The Operational Risk team is responsible for the development and implementation of the Group's Operational Risk Management Framework. In this role you will be responsible for:
 Create an Operating Model for the NFR Reporting Capability that is focussed on Data Management activities focussing specifically on Operational Risk and Compliance (OR&C);
 Responsible for the implementation of all aspects of data governance and data quality for the OR&C data scope;
 Has specialist knowledge of their data elements and ensures they are compliant with data management policies and standards;
 Responsible for the identification, definition, lineage and documentation of critical data elements in accordance with group standards;
 Identifies data quality issues and works with relevant stakeholders to design and monitor their resolution and remediation;
 Responsible for the reporting and monitoring of open RiskInsite items. Approve closure of items;
 Work closely with the Group Data Office as well as the Risk Data Office to ensure input is provided to policies and frameworks as well as the toolsets used for the management of Data;
 Establish regular reporting and monitoring activities on the status of data quality across OR&C and track progress in terms of resolution;
 Assist Business Unit teams with the prioritisation of data management resolution activities as set out in the data management implementation framework;
 Educate senior stakeholders across OR&C about the data management activities and the importance thereof;
 Review and propose system changes to RiskInSite (OR&C risk system) to ensure data quality is maintained or enhanced and the impact on reporting clearly understood.
 Skills and Experience
 Exposure to data quality tools (e.g. Collibra, AbInitio) [desirable]
 Sound knowledge in Teradata, alongside SQL , Tableau, etc.
 Excellent data analysis and reporting skills with knowledge of analytics
 Experience in Data Management activities and managing various stakeholder groups
 Implementation experience of BCBS239 is preferred
 Key interest in data visualisation and innovation in data analytics
 Experience in setting up governance structures and operating models to help deliver sustainable data management activities
 Experience in building and supporting a new team grow is preferred
 Track record of continuous improvement initiatives is preferred
 Strong computer literacy, with advanced skills in MS Office products such as Excel, Power Point
 Ability to work independently and to prioritise, manage and meet challenging deadlines
 Skills in Open Pages, Cognos, SQL, SAS and Tableau preferred
