$80,669 - $92,150 (plus super) 
 Osborne, SA 
 Naval Construction Branch (NCB) aims to be recognised as the critical driver in the delivery of capability to Navy within the national shipbuilding enterprise. The long-term, continuous build program outlined in Government’s Naval Shipbuilding Plan of 2017 requires Defence to take a new approach in the waterfront management of ship and submarine construction and that is why NCB are calling for applications from talented, motivated and skilled people to drive this critical national agenda. 

The Business Cost Analyst will be required to work in a complex operating environment as part of the NCB, which is headquartered in Adelaide. The position supports the implementation and delivery of continuous shipbuilding and will be an integral part of the Business Cost Team and will have an opportunity to embed business cost processes, ensuring a clear and consistent approach that aligns with management accounting activities. 

The routine business activities that the role will undertake includes analysis of costs, preparation of reports and briefs, auditing of business transactions and engagement with external and internal stakeholders to secure financial and costing information for assurance purposes.


The key responsibilities for the Business Cost Analyst are: 

 Assess cost claims for completeness, accuracy and compliance with contracts, laws, financial regulations and policies; 
 Provide assistance in the management of establishing budgets for effective reporting and forecasting which includes investigation and analysis of data and providing accurate and timely performance information to stakeholders; 
 Assist the team to collect data and compile reports for line management to identify actual performance in the shipyard aimed at meeting Budget and Schedule; 
 Provide the costing rationale and justification of procurement and contract proposals by evaluating data and information to produce recommendations in accordance with organisational requirements including alignment to budgets; 
 Contribute to the delivery of the NCB Strategic Plan in relation to cost activities by assisting with the development, review and implementation of processes and systems to support current and future business requirements. 
 To succeed in this role you must have personal drive and integrity with the ability to: 
 Comply with organisational values and behaviours and have a shared responsibility for the achievement of team goals and objectives; 
 Add value and deliver on the organisational strategy; 
 Build trust and demonstrate integrity with internal and external stakeholders; 
 Support the NCB leadership team by monitoring and effectively reporting the progress of assigned tasking in a timely manner; 
 Communicate effectively with stakeholders at various organisational levels and across teams; 
 Willingness to learn and ability to prioritise tasks based on organisational requirements.

Technical Business Analyst 

 Identify opportunities to build new and innovative technology solutions for the organisation
 Flexible and dynamic work environment
 Located in the heart of the CBD 
 The Opportunity: 

We are looking for a proactive, analytical and solutions focussed Business Analyst. You will have the opportunity to analyse the current state and help create innovative, highly usable solutions by bridging the gap between internal clients, technology enabled process change and solution delivery.
 You will join our National Information & Digital team, working in close partnership with our Technology Solutions Lead and Platforms/Development teams. 

 You will: 

 Detect gaps in processes, identify innovation and optimisation opportunities to facilitate and lead process change meetings with key stakeholders; 
 Effectively gather and document requirements, design business processes & align solutions to business objectives; 
 Facilitate relationships between Business and Technology teams to identify opportunities for improvement in business operations & processes; 
 Review & manage business test lifecycles from User Acceptance through to Post Implementation; 
 Be involved in the design or modification of business or IT systems; 
 Liaise with system architects and developers; 
 Coordinate testing of solutions systems and creation of user manuals. 

 About You: 

 Bachelor’s Degree of equivalent experience; 
 5+ years’ experience as a Technical Business Analyst or equivalent; 
 Ability to create end to end process flows and identify key areas of optimization; 
 Strong understanding of ITIL process; 
 Ability to effectively prioritise work and deliver to tight deadlines; 
 Strong analytical & problem-solving skills; 
 Intermediate knowledge of SQL schemas, queries and data dictionaries; 
 Intermediate usage of Excel including Macros, VLookups, Index Lookups; 
 Intermediate experience with SharePoint, OneDrive & Workflows; 
 Exposure to JIRA or Azure DevOps for work management; 
 Effective communication with project stakeholders. 

