 Permanent opportunity for a software focused Business Analyst 
 City fringe location - close to public transport and street parking 
 Enjoy additional leave days - 'ME' leave and 'Volunteer' leave 
 About the Role: 

As a Technical Business Analyst at Compare the Market, you will review information and processes in order to improve, document and to design changes to applications and systems, working very closely with an on-shore Software Development team. The Business Analyst will work autonomously to solve problems and drive outcomes that are consistent with the Technology road map in support of the overall Business strategy. 

 Key accountabilities include: 
 Lead the continual analysis, review and improvement of processes as well as knowledge transfer to build collective expertise; 
 Support and improve business analysis practices and facilitate cultural change towards a more integrated and aligned Development function across all of Compare the Market’s systems and products; 
 Act as a bridge between business problems and technology solutions; 
 Early and continuous engagement with key stakeholders to achieve the best possible outcomes; 
 Professionally escalate concerns regarding delivery issues or problems; 
 Analysing and documenting business processes and workflows; 
 Documenting business requirements; 
 Translating business requirements into technical and functional requirements; 
 Develop User Stories and Business Requirements to support software development; 
 Work with product stakeholders and subject matter experts to elicit accurate information for use in requirements documentation; 
 Act as a key point of contact between business stakeholders and development teams; 
 Use a variety of techniques including group sessions and one on one interviews to capture and document requirements; 
 Assist Technical teams with analysis of data flows, process mapping, workshop facilitation, data analysis; 
 In conjunction with your peers, maximise service delivery through deep and thorough analysis of our data sources, these could be APIs, databases, analytics sources, and documentation; 
 Testing and validating that the solution implemented by the development team is consistent with the technical specifications; 
 Fully implement, and ensure the requirements conform within the Company’s risk management, governance, and compliance frameworks; 
 Develop and maintain a customer focused relationship with the product stakeholders and other information technology areas by collaboration, timely communication and responsiveness. 


 Knowledge and Experience: 

Essential 
 Formal qualifications in a relevant area and/or commensurate experience; 
 Solid experience in an analyst or technical role in a software development environment and commensurate knowledge and understanding of Agile or traditional software development methodologies; 
 Understanding of the software development life cycle; 
 Outstanding written and verbal communication skills; 
 Fast learner with outstanding problem solving skills; 
 A natural curiosity in how things work 

 Preferred 
 Experience in the banking sector 


 Who are Compare the Market: 

Since launching in Australia in 2012, Compare the Market has become one of Australia’s most loved comparison websites. 

Our 200+ employees work towards helping Australians make quick and easy purchase decisions about a number of important insurance, financial and household products; from insurance and energy to credit cards and home loans. 

 Our Benefits: 
 City fringe location - close to public transport and street parking; 
 Enjoy additional leave days - ‘ME’ leave and ‘Volunteer Day’ leave; 
 Join our vibrant social and community activities including annual celebration, family fun days and regular events across each of our sites; 
 Study support (up to 50% of tuition fees for relevant courses) and professional membership reimbursement; 
 Employee discounts on Car, Home, Travel insurance; 
 Income protection insurance provided to support you in the event of non-work related illness or injury; 
 Discounts with a broad range of providers, including gym memberships, accommodation, dental care and more. 


If you are seeking a new challenge and would enjoy the opportunity to work in a growing and changing business, click on the APPLY NOW button and submit your application. 

 Compare the Market welcome and value diversity in the workplace. 

 A note from Compare the Market to recruitment agencies: We politely ask that you avoid making any approaches or sending any unsolicited resumes to our Recruitment Team or Hiring Leaders across our business. Compare the Market is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes. 

