 ARC  is currently assisting a successful natural energy resource provider who has a strong reputation in leading the way of the international resources sector, who are currently seeking an  Organisational Change Management (OCM) Specialist and Business Analyst. 

 The Position Description: 
The Organisational Change Management (OCM) Specialist & Business Analyst plays a critical role within their Project Hub activities for their Fixed Plant projects, with an initial focus on delivery of a discrete package of work for the Value Tracking Team in a Business Analyst capacity. The Value Tracking part of the role, you will be required to manage and lead a short piece of work initially to standardise and simplify benefits/value calculations required for Fixed Plant projects. This tool will provide a standardised way of calculating cost savings, and translation of equipment downtime reductions into volume related improvements. 

 The Role 
As an  OCM Specialist , you will be required to manage and coordinate ongoing Organisational Change Management (OCM) efforts within Fixed Plant - Projects Hub. This role will require you to: 
 Own, maintain and develop the OCM framework, tools and templates; 
 Monitor all Projects on adherence to the framework; 
 Provide day to day support to project teams with OCM activities from project initiation through to deployment. This includes, but not limited to Stakeholder Analyses, advice on optimal stakeholder engagement approaches / tactics, preparation and facilitation of Change Impact Assessments, development of communications and engagement plans, development of communications and change artefacts, completion of capability and readiness assessments, coordination and delivery of training / knowledge transfer. 
 Support with the scoping and mobilisation of new Fixed Plant Projects, completing all necessary OCM activities and managing all required Stakeholder Engagement and Communications up to project kick-off; 
 Provide ad hoc support with project / program email announcements, presentations, memos and workshops which are professional and on-brand; 
 Prepare and present OCM updates for regular meetings; 
 Develop and deliver a Communications and Engagement Plan for the whole Program holistically; 
 Identify, mitigate and manage risks to change management, communications & engagement; and 
 Maintain relationships with key stakeholders, seeking candid feedback at regular intervals and putting action plans in place to address any issues or concerns 
 Conduct workshops to gather and prioritise requirements for a standardised calculation tool for Fixed Plant projects; 
 Work with Data Scientists to guide development develop the tool and supporting logic to perform the required calculations based on these prioritised requirements; 
 Perform quality review and testing activities; 
 Work with stakeholders to seek agreement on the calculation methodologies and approval for the finished tool; 
 Develop guidelines, process flows, templates and other documentation to support the tool and new way of working; and 
 Manage the implementation of the new tool, processes and documentation into Fixed Plant projects through knowledge sharing, training and coaching activities 

 Required Skills and Experience 
 Minimum 2 years in a Professional Management Consulting environment (or similar) supporting the delivery of programs and projects; 
 Experience in Organisational Change Management (OCM) is required; 
 Experience in Project Management and managing the delivery of discrete work packages highly desirable; 
 Proven track record of identifying and estimating benefits, conducting value analysis and developing business cases in in complex asset intensive organisations; 
 Experience in performing value analysis in a maintenance context is highly desirable; 
 Experience in developing process/guideline documentation for project team members within a program environment; 
 Experience supporting tool/software/code development by undertaking business analysis, quality assurance/testing and change management responsibilities; 
 Highly developed oral and written communication and presentation skills; 
 Must be a self-starter, taking initiative and able to work autonomously, executing tasks independently with minimal guidance; 
 Proven ability to manage competing priorities and multiple pieces of work; 
 Ability to be flexible and adapt quickly to changing requirements; 
 Proven ability to engage and build relationships with stakeholders at all levels of seniority; 
 Excellent working knowledge of MS Office products (PowerPoint, Word and Excel); and 
 Ability to work to tight timeframes in a complex and demanding environment. 

 What to expect in return: 
Dedicated to providing their staff with the best opportunities for professional development, they are offering a competitive contract daily rate on an  initial 12 month contract  which will be extended for the right candidate. 

This is a Monday to Friday role based in the  Brisbane CBD  that is offering flexible working arrangements. 

